   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   NASHVILLE-TOURISM _ NASHVILLE _ Hoping to broaden its appeal to
tourists, Nashville opens the 1.2-million-square foot
entertainment, shopping center Opry Mills at the former site of
Opryland today (Thursday). It will feature 200 stores, ranging from
Blacklion to the Rainforest Cafe and the Bass Pro Shop Outdoor
World. (DuBose, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   METHODISTS _ CLEVELAND _ Daily coverage, as merits, of United
Methodist General Conference in Cleveland. Issues coming up this
week are same-sex blessing, a new TV ad campaign to rival the
Mormons, legislation apologizing for the denomination's past racism
and trying to raise a huge amount of money for historically black
Methodist colleges that include Clark Atlanta U., some
denominational reorganization, and possible resolutions on Elian
and gun control, to name a few. (GWhite, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-CONDITIONING _ As a rule of thumb, you should use your air
conditioners as little as possible because cooling your house
generally costs even more than heating it. Getting the most out of
the money you spend on air conditioning requires many of the same
measures you use to increase your home's energy efficiency in
winter. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 22.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is James Cummings Nuts &AMP; Bolts Column.
</P>
