   SAFRICA-MARKETS (Johannesburg) _ For years, the Johannesburg
Stock Exchange was nearly as notorious among international
financiers as the country itself was among human rights advocates.
Now, a decade after the country began a remarkable political
transformation, South Africa's markets have found that they, too,
must transform. Backed by a new law, regulators have taken aim at
insider traders. By Henri E. Cauvin.
