   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily marketplace column.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stocks were sharply lower in early trading.
At 11:15 a.m., the Dow Jones industrial average was down 1.34
percent, the S&AMP;P 500 down 1.63 percent and the Nasdaq composite
index down 4.18 percent. Shares of Cisco Systems fell 6.5 percent
after the company warned late Tuesday that a parts shortage will
hurt profit. Motorola shares dropped as much as 12 percent after a
Salomon Smith Barney analyst cut his rating on the stock. Treasury
prices were modestly higher. European stock markets were lower:
London down 0.17 percent and Frankfurt down 2.27 percent. Tokyo's
Nikkei closed down 0.80 percent; the Hang Seng in Hong Kong ended
down 1.92 percent. By Robert D. Hershey Jr.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-TAX (Washington) _ The House Commerce Committee is
scheduled to vote on extending a moratorium on any Internet
taxation until 2006. By Lizette Alvarez.
</P>
