   BETTY-FRIEDAN (Washington) _ In 1963, Betty Friedan, the
combative writer and activist, inspired a social revolution for
women with ``The Feminine Mystique,'' in which she debunked the
myth of the postwar woman. It sold more than three million copies.
In her sixth book and first memoir, ``Life So Far'' she recounts a
turbulent personal history. By Alex Witchel.
</P>
