two leading auction houses, Sotheby's and Christie's, are embroiled
in an embarrassing price-fixing scandal, Phillips, which is based
in London, is causing a considerable stir with its conspicuous and
costly effort to reinvent itself as a major player in New York. By
Christopher Mason.
</P>
