<DOCNO> NYT20000510.0084 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-10 14:48 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0994 &Cx1f; tie-z
u a BC-CIRCUITS-BUDGET-NYT &LR;      05-10 0417
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CIRCUITS-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Circuits stories from The N.Y. Times News Service for Thursday,
May 11:
</P>
<P>
   CIR-ONLINE-SURVEY (Undated) _ A new survey of Internet usage
shows the Internet is not socially isolating, but improves social
networks. Also, it shows that women are gaining on men in Internet
usage. By Rebecca Fairley Raney.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-BILL-ONLINE (Undated) _ Paying bills on-line. Not just web
banking, but sites that collect your bills, post them on a secure
web page for you to view, and pay them, deducting money from your
checking account. By Roy Furchgott.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT2.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-PRODUCT-TESTS (Undated) _ Using simulated humans, the most
well-known of which is called Jack, to test products from tractors
to car trunks. By Daniel Sorid.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, NYT3,4.
</P>
