than he did while doing the unthinkable to the Red Sox. By Bob
Duffy. 800 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BBA-WHITESOX-THOMAS (Boston) _ Indecisiveness about his
first-base assignment and a series of injuries plagued Frank (The
Big Hurt) Thomas.But this season it's different. By Bob Duffy. 960
words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-HARGROVE (New York) _ What happened to Mike Hargrove last
December _ when he was fired as Indians manager despite winning
five straight AL Central titles _ was a reminder that there is no
substitute for winning world championships. By Larry Whiteside. 900
words.
</P>
