<P>
   SIERRA-LEONE-U.N. (United Nations) _ With its political options
all but exhausted, the United Nations on Wednesday ordered its
peacekeeping troops in Sierra Leone to take up defensive positions
and prepare for a pitched battle against the rebel fighters
advancing toward the capital, Freetown. ``We'll do what we have to
do to defend ourselves and the government,'' the U.N. spokesman,
Fred Eckhard, said. ``We hope it won't come to a pitched battle,
but we are preparing for one.'' By Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS (Moscow) _ President Vladimir Putin named
Mikhail Kasyanov, his chief foreign-debt negotiator and a liberal
economics expert, as his prime minister on Wednesday, a
long-predicted move some said bodes well for efforts to tame
Russia's feral style of capitalism. That view was bolstered by a
separate report Wednesday that Putin may abolish the government's
fuel and energy ministry as part of a restructuring of his Cabinet.
The immensely powerful agency has often been attacked as a seat of
political corruption and a brake on capitalist reforms. By Michael
Wines.
</P>
