   NATIONAL GENERAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-EDWARDS (New Orleans) _ As a jury considers how much former
Gov. Edwin W. Edwards should pay for his crimes, people in New
Orleans considered what his corruption conviction means. Many said
they expected that little would change. Politics as usual would be
politics as usually. The only reason Edwards was caught, several
people said, was because he was no longer in power. By Kevin Sack.
</P>
