   ELIAN-KIDS _ ATLANTA _ The central question before the federal
appeals court on Thursday is, can a 6-y-o make a complicated
decision about different political cultures. Bigger question for
6-year-olds is can they spell asylum? Looking to present a voices
sort of piece here -- either in story or grafic form -- that relies
on smart writing and is based on interviews with other 6-year-olds
about their knowledge of words like asylum , parolee and other
words that have come up in reference to Elian. Will be based on two
days of interviews in schools with crosssectin of kids, including,
we hope, some Cuban-American kids. (Bixler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
