from Jacksonville to West Palm Beach by 2005. Also, Amtrak will
have four daily trains from Miami to Orlando, carrying an estimated
625,000 riders per year, according to a plan they released today at
the request of DOT officials. Not only will there be a
Miami-to-Orlando train, but a Tampa-to-Orlando one and a
Tampa-to-Miami route. (McGinness, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   RAP-FIGHT _ A fight erupted backstage during a hip-hop concert
at the FleetCenter, and at least six people were injured, one
critically. One person was arrested in the Monday night fight.
(Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   Also moving in (e) entertainment category
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft is due to respond by Tuesday
to the government's proposed remedies in the antitrust case against
the software company. (Glass, Cox News Service). 22.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-MUSEUM _ LONDON _ The Tate Museum _ London's first
full-fledged museum of modern art opens its doors at the end of the
week. Queen Elizabeth will preside at the opening on Thursday in
what is a converted power station across the Thames from St Paul's
Cathedral. It is already getting rave reviews. Developing.
(Roughton, Cox News Service). 20. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
