<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-10 18:09 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1170 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP11-COX     05-10 0476
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Death by chocolate, sour cream
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When Gidget Erwin of Smyrna, Ga. requested a chocolate cake with
sour cream in both the cake and frosting, it conjured a distant
memory for Eleanor Ragsdale, who sent this recipe from a book
published by the San Francisco Junior League.
</P>
<P>
   Ragsdale says her husband made the cake just once _ for her
birthday 20 years ago _ but she remembers the occasion.
</P>
<P>
   ``And if memory serves me correctly,'' she says, ``it is
delicious.''
</P>
<P>
   Our tester agreed: It looks good, tastes great and freezes
beautifully.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Sour Cream
</P>
<P>
   Chocolate Cake
</P>
<P>
   Makes 12 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 30 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 25-30 minutes
</P>
<P>
   For the cake:
</P>
<P>
   2 cups unsifted all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   2 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   1 cup water
</P>
<P>
   2 large eggs
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces unsweetened baking chocolate, melted
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup ( 1/2 stick) butter
</P>
<P>
   1 1/4 teaspoons baking soda
</P>
<P>
   For the frosting:
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup (1 stick) butter
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces unsweetened baking chocolate, chopped
</P>
<P>
   4 cups confectioners' sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 9-inch or
three 8-inch round cake pans; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   For the cake: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, salt,
sugar, vanilla, water, eggs, sour cream, chocolate, butter and
baking soda. Beat with mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping
sides of bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes at highest speed. Pour
into pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until tester inserted near center
of layer comes out clean. Remove from the oven and cool on a rack.
</P>
<P>
   For the frosting: In the top of a double boiler set over barely
simmering water, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly.
(Or melt chocolate and butter in microwave oven on high for 1 to 1
1/2 minutes.) Remove from heat and cool. Add confectioners' sugar,
then blend in sour cream and vanilla and beat until smooth.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 648 calories, 7 grams protein, 30 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 42), 96 grams carbohydrates, 99
milligrams cholesterol, 436 milligrams sodium, 1 gram fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Request
</P>
<P>
   Catherine Potter wants a recipe for ice cream parfait pie made
with Jell-O.
</P>
<P>
   Sheila Godwin is eager to find a recipe for Vidalia onion jelly.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting this column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests to be published in this column should be
sent to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Fax:
404-526-5509. Include a daytime phone number. E-mail:
mlanghenry(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Marcia Langhenry writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
