r l BC-SHOPPING-GUIDE11-COX     05-10 0848
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOPPING-GUIDE11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Last year at Target, we bought the bird food Squirrel Away.
It has an ingredient that keeps squirrels from pigging out on
whatever you put in the bird feeders. Target no longer carries this
item. Any suggestions?
</P>
<P>
   _ Randy and Teresa Mills, Fayetteville , Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Soon, those pesky squirrels will have to dine elsewhere.
Squirrel Away, which is mixed in with bird feed, is a natural,
safe, nonviolent way of discouraging squirrels. Home Depot carries
it in selected stores. We found ours at 815 Sidney Marcus Blvd.
N.E. (404-231-1411). A 3-ounce package is $3.96 and treats 50
pounds of seed. You can also order online at www.squirrelaway.com
or call 1-800-229-5454. Two 3-ounce packages are $9.95 and include
shipping and handling.
</P>
<P>
   Squirrel Away is made from peppers that are full of vitamins,
proteins and lipids. They also contain capsaicin, the natural
substance that makes peppers spicy. It's distasteful to mammals,
including squirrels, chipmunks and raccoons, but attractive to
birds.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When my husband and I lived in Pittsburgh, we could find
Frank's RedHot Hot Sauce but not the RedHot Buffalo Wing Sauce. And
we can't find it here. The sauce also makes a great marinade for
grilled boneless chicken breast. Best of all, it's fat-free. Any
ideas?
</P>
<P>
   _ June McKeon,
</P>
<P>
   Alpharetta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: This request was almost too hot to handle. Like many food
items, Frank's RedHot Buffalo Wing Sauce has limited distribution
in the Northeast and Midwest. And it's quite limited in the South.
However, you can order it directly from the company, Reckitt
Benckiser: 1-800-456-9477. A 12-ounce bottle is $2.49. The
manufacturer says the sauce ``is specially prepared so you can
easily re-create the great taste of restaurant-style wings at
home.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Wash &AMP; Curl shampoo. I bought it over a year
ago, but now it's nowhere to be found.
</P>
<P>
   _ Debbie Bowen, Dawsonville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   And another curly question: I am looking for Wash &AMP; Curl by
Nutra Care. I have used it for years, but now I can't find it.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mary Ann Miller, Peachtree City, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Trying to find this shampoo is enough to make your hair curl.
But we persevered and found it at Drug Emporium, 1543 Ga. 138 in
Conyers (770-929-0274). An 8-ounce bottle is $3.29. Made for fine,
limp, dry hair, this shampoo, says manufacturer Nutra Care, ``will
leave your hair fresh and clean and provide the most beautiful
curls with body, bounce and resilience after styling.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: For many years, I have been a fan of Fracas perfume, but
lately I have not been able to find it. Do they still make it? My
husband gave me this perfume when we were engaged in 1950. That's
why I am deeply attached to it.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mary Mueller, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Fans of this fragrance from French designer Robert Piguet are
legion and include Madonna, Kim Basinger, Martha Stewart and
Courtney Love. The white floral _ consisting of tuberose, jasmine,
jonquil, lily of the valley, white iris _ first hit counters in
1948, dropped out of sight in the United States in the '80s, then
was relaunched in 1996. For a limited time, the company is offering
a 1.7-ounce eau de parfum spray and 4-ounce body lotion in a black
evening bag trimmed with white flowers ($55). Look for it at
Scentimentals, 9700 Medlock Bridge Road, Duluth (678-417-0422) You
can also buy the fragrance separately at Neiman Marcus in Lenox
Square (404-266-8200). A 1/4-ounce parfum is $75; a 1.7-ounce eau
de parfum spray is $60.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you please help us find the embroidered cotton shirt
called a guayabera in size XL. These shirts come in pastels and
white and are worn loosely over trousers. No one in the Georgia
mountains seems to know what we want, and our husbands are about to
wear out their old ones.
</P>
<P>
   _ Alice Green and Shirley Paul
</P>
<P>
   A: This summer, your spouses will be stylish and dapper in their
guayaberas. Made of cotton, these short-sleeved sport shirts were
originally worn by men in Cuba. They have large front pockets and
are trimmed with embroidery and tucks. We discovered our shirt
($7.95) at Haband Outlet, 2105 LaVista Road N.E. (404-633-1993). It
comes in pastels and white and is available in sizes up to 3X.
Similar shirts are known as Mexican wedding shirts, because grooms
wear them for weddings in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
