<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MICROSOFT CRAFTS ITS OWN ANTITRUST REMEDY
 &HT;    680&AMP;add. Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
 &HT;    By ANDREW J. GLASS
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Responding to a federal judge's order, Microsoft
Corp. on Wednesday rejected calls for a breakup and instead offered
to impose curbs on its business practices that it claimed ``fully
redresses the antitrust violations found by the court.''
</P>
<P>
   In its filing, announced after the close of the major financial
