federal judge to immediately throw out the government's proposal to
break the company in two, arguing that ``the laws and the facts do
not support such a radical step.'' At the same time, the company
laid out a series of narrow proposals it says are more appropriate
than a breakup in addressing the anticompetitive actions found by
