<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Al Gore has a great deal to say
about a lot of issues in this campaign, but the manner in which he
says them may at times lose rather than win votes. For all his
years in politics, he often uses old arm-waving, floor-stomping,
pre-television techniques while George W. Bush campaigns with a
cool, confident expression and a modulated voice. Style may not win
elections. But it can help. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Already filed.)
