 PERSONALS: Better Buttons Mean Better Business 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news &LR; 
 &UR; file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The University of Missouri Hospital, which has undertaken a study
of the relative beauty of belly buttons, photographed the navels of
147 women and asked a panel of doctors and nurses to judge them
aesthetically.
</P>
<P>
   The most attractive ones, reports Allure magazine, were ``small
and had a tiny T-shaped indentation. Vertical, oval-shaped navels
also scored higher than round, horizontal ones, and innies scored
higher than outies.''
</P>
<P>
   Plastic surgeon  &UR; C. Lin Puckett &LR; , who conducted the study, said,
``The next challenge is to define the surgical technique that will
result in the ideal.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Former romantic  &UR; Mark Steinberg &LR;  isn't surprised that the
``ILOVEYOU'' virus has caused such problems, because he remembers a
number of times ``when those three words were responsible for
wiping out everything I'd saved.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_  &UR; Jeanne Moreau &LR;  will play  &UR; Marguerite Duras &LR;  in a movie version
of ``That Love,'' a book about the French writer's affair with a
younger man, the novel's author.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; STEWART'S ROLE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   At a party when  &UR; Arthur Miller &LR; 's ``The Ride Down Mount Morgan''
opened on Broadway, star  &UR; Patrick Stewart &LR;  left in a huff when he
realized that all the hors d'oeuvres were cold; he said he'd been
promised hot snacks. This may have been a bad omen.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart, whose contract with the Shubert Organization, producers
of the show, provides him with a share of its profits, returned to
the stage after curtain calls one recent Saturday to criticize the
producers for not spending enough on promoting the play.
</P>
<P>
   This resulted in Shubert's lodging a formal complaint with
Actors' Equity against their star, whom they are accusing of
unprofessional conduct.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BETTER LIVING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Ronald Barlow &LR; 's ``The Vanishing American Outhouse'' (Viking;
$19.95) reveals that Alaska has more outhouses than any other state
in the union.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _  &UR; Kim Cattrall &LR;  of ``Sex and the City'' told  &UR; Baird Jones &LR;  at a
party at Cartier's in Manhattan last week that ``having a beauty
mark'' near her mouth ``has changed my life because it made me feel
vulnerable.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _  &UR; Carolyn Kizer &LR;  forwards the martini menu of Fedora, one of the
most elegant restaurants in Kansas City, which features among its
crimes against martini nature: the Hazelnut Martini, the Chocolate
Martini and the Creamsicle Martini.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``He's a great athlete. He's always been very disciplined and &LR; 
 &UR; very determined about training and working out. And I think &LR; 
 &UR; that's important. I think he understands the value of good &LR; 
 &UR; health.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Laura Bush &LR;  in response to Glamour magazine's question about
what young women should know about her husband, the presidential
candidate.
</P>
