<SLUG> BC-FBO-AVENGERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROCKY START STUNS AVENGERS' BROCK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Avengers' season is rapidly deteriorating and
no one is more surprised than coach Stan Brock.
</P>
<P>
   ``No doubt about it. In my wildest dreams I never thought we'd
be 0-4,'' Brock said. ``I'm not happy about it, but I understand
where we are.''
</P>
<P>
   The misery figures to continue tonight at 6, when the winless
Avengers face the Arizona Rattlers (3-1) at America West Arena in
Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps in a sign of the team's spiraling fortunes, Brock will
give former Raiders and USC quarterback Todd Marinovich his first
start of the season over Scott Semptimphelter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Todd's going to start for me. Just for a changeup,'' Brock
said. ``It's nothing Scott has or has not done. We just need a
change.''
</P>
<P>
   It will be Marinovich's first start in professional football
since Nov. 8, 1992, when he started for the Raiders.
</P>
<P>
   Marinovich made his first appearance of the season last week,
completing 15 of 30 passes for 168 yards, three touchdowns and one
interception in a 65-44 loss to Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a long time since I've played a full game,''
Marinovich said. ``I'm looking forward to getting into a rhythm out
there. It's tough to do when you just play a quarter here and a
quarter there.''
</P>
<P>
   By comparison, Semptimphelter has completed 67 of 126 passes for
806 yards with 13 touchdowns and four interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, if we were 4-0, I wouldn't be making any changes,''
Brock said. ``I've already changed the wide receivers, the
offensive line and defensive specialists. I'm trying to make
changes to make us a better football team. We're building. That's
what I'm here for.''
</P>
<P>
   It's too early to say the Avengers are the worst team in the
league, although they seem headed in that direction. Under the
Arena Football League's own power rankings, the Avengers are the
third-worst team, ahead of the Houston ThunderBears and the Buffalo
Destroyers.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't matter who we play. Our opponent is the situation
we're in right now,'' Brock said. ``It's not going to happen
overnight.''
</P>
<P>
   AVENGERS vs. ARIZONA
</P>
<P>
   Kickoff: 6 p.m., America West Arena.
</P>
<P>
   TV/Radio: The Nashville Network (delayed, 9 p.m.); KMPC-AM
(1540).
</P>
<P>
   Avengers (0-4) update: The Avengers will make a quarterback
change, inserting Todd Marinovich in place of Scott Semptimphelter,
but L.A. has a lot of other problems to correct before earning the
franchise's first victory. The Avengers have the second-worst
scoring defense in the league, allowing 58.2 points per game.
</P>
<P>
   Arizona (3-1) update: The Rattlers are led by former Cal State
Northridge quarterback Sherdrick Bonner, who has thrown 24
touchdown passes with just four interceptions. The Rattlers have
won two Arena Football championships.
</P>
<P>
   -Scott Wolf
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-10-00 2235EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
